---
import '../styles/global.css';

const pageTitle = "AstroBlog";
---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/first-astro/favicon.svg" />
		<link rel="icon" href="/first-astro/favicon.ico" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>{pageTitle}</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		
        <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + ""} >Home</a>
        <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "/about/"} >About</a>
        <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "/blog/"} >Blog</a>

		<h1>{pageTitle}</h1>

		<p>Welcome to the freaking blog. Can't I write in markdown?? Whats with all this html? <br>
           Turns out those are in separate .md files. This is all still html.
        </p>

        <h2>My Astro Learning Blog</h2>
        <p>This is where I will post about my journey learning Astro.</p>
        <ul>
            <li><a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "/posts/post-1/"}>Post 1</a></li>
	        <li><a href= {import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "/posts/post-2/"}>Post 2</a></li>
    	    <li><a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL + "/posts/post-3/"}>Post 3</a></li>		
        </ul>

	</body>
</html>
